Business Brief -- H.B. Fuller Co.:
   Net Income Advances 65%,
   Topping Analysts' Forecasts
Fuller cited improved profit margins from better plant use
and lower raw-material costs, as well as controls on
operating expenses. Earnings improved at its North American,
Asian and Latin American operations but declined
"significantly" in Europe.
   Fuller released the earnings after the market's close. But
on a day when the market drifted downward, Fuller climbed $3
in national over-the-counter trading to $71.